- # Rendered inside the Canvas iframe. Stance-neutral on signed-in
- # state because the iframe's cookie jar is partitioned away from the
- # top-level dashboard session — we genuinely can't tell whether the
- # user is signed in elsewhere. The button opens a new tab via
- # target=_blank rather than navigating the Canvas page away, so the
- # instructor can keep Canvas in place; the rest of the launch flow
- # (and any needed Wikipedia OAuth) happens in the new tab where
- # session cookies behave as first-party.
.lti-iframe__landing
  = image_tag '/assets/images/wiki-logo.png', alt: 'Wiki Education Dashboard', class: 'lti-iframe__logo'
  = link_to "/lti/connect_course?ltik=#{CGI.escape(@ltik.to_s)}",
            target: '_blank', rel: 'noopener',
            class: 'button dark lti-iframe__button' do
    = t('lti.iframe_landing.button', default: 'Open the Wiki Education Dashboard')
    %span.icon.icon-z-external-link_white{ 'aria-hidden': 'true' }
